Former governor of Kaduna state, Alhaji Balarabe Musa and the Kwara state governorship candidate of the Labour Party in the 2019  general election, Comrade Issa Aremu has taken a swipe on the leadership of the country, saying Nigeria is suffering from crisis of governances. The spoke during a joint press conference a in Kaduna. Aremu said the ultimate goal of the National Consultative Front (NCF) is political but added that its membership are drawn from diverse political parties and interest groups. He noted that the establishment of the front connects to the daily struggles of Nigerians against crisis of governance, noting that any crisis within a ruling party must be of grave concern because of it’s adverse implications for good governance. “A ruling party in crisis  means actually a nation in “governance hemorrhage” he stressed. According to Aremu, “there is no doubt that National Consultative Front (NCF) is an idea whose time has come. Things are fast falling apart in Nigeria beyond what the late literary icon, Chinua Achebe documented about colonial Nigeria in the classic African story: Things Fall Apart and post colonial Nigeria’s “The Trouble with Nigeria. “It is a new political paradigm to get things done in a new way to  deliver the much needed public good to Nigerians. Therefore the facilitating Secretariat of the National Consultative Front (NCF) must intensify consultation with all to retain confidence. In the new political normal, we should not take each other for granted just as the Nigerians have been taken for a ride since 1999.